<p class="">    <h2>Key Challenges in the Eri Silks Market</h2>    <ul>        <li>            <strong>Supply Chain Disruptions:</strong> The Eri silks market faces significant challenges due to disruptions in the supply chain, which can stem from natural disasters, political instability, or the impact of global pandemics. Such disruptions can lead to inconsistent quality and availability of raw materials.        </li>        <li>            <strong>Limited Awareness:</strong> There is a general lack of awareness about the benefits and unique properties of Eri silks compared to other types of silk. This poses a challenge in attracting a broader consumer base, particularly in regions where silk is less known.        </li>        <li>            <strong>High Production Costs:</strong> The labor-intensive process of Eri silk production contributes to higher costs. Farmers and producers face difficulties with maintaining profitability due to fluctuations in market prices and increased production expenses.        </li>        <li>            <strong>Environmental Concerns:</strong> The Eri silk industry is also under scrutiny for its environmental impact, particularly concerning deforestation and the carbon footprint associated with sericulture. This can affect brand reputation and consumer preference.        </li>        <li>            <strong>Competition from Synthetic Fibers:</strong> The rise of synthetic fabrics, which are often cheaper and more readily available, presents a substantial challenge. Consumers may opt for these alternatives over natural Eri silk, impacting demand.        </li>    </ul>    <h2>Potential Growth Opportunities in the Eri Silks Market</h2>    <ul>        <li>            <strong>Consumer Education Initiatives:</strong> Implementing targeted marketing and education campaigns that highlight the unique qualities and sustainability aspects of Eri silk can help raise consumer awareness and drive demand.        </li>        <li>            <stron